title: Official Deadlines Homeworks
body:
I would like to know when is the deadline of every homework?

I thought were every tuesday as CS101 course, and today I realize that solutions of homework 2 has been released.

I am aware about the deadlines are not so strict as last course CS101, but I would like to deliver every homework at time stablished by the course.

Thanks in advance!

i is out of range

for i in range(0, len(nor)):
    norm = norm + nor[i]
    rot = rot+ro[i]

for example, nor="123",len=3, than range is 0,1,2,3, but you have only 3 letters in rot.

s="abc"
print s[4]

Will also give string index out of range. You are trying to access an index of a string which is not there.

The solution videos will be posted Monday 23:59 UTC, so just before midnight that night. The first week's solution videos were posted one day late because the homework itself was posted one day late, and we wanted to give people a full week before posting the solution videos. Hope this helps!
And again, just to reiterate, there is absolutely no penalty for submitting after the solution videos are up.

title: Is there an alternative to typing our HTML into long strings?
body: Something about doing that just feels kinda messy and it makes things harder to read since it messes up syntax highlighting in text editors. I can't help but think that this is done for the sake of simplicity in keeping everything in one file but I dunno, is this really how you write stuff in google app engine and for web apps in general?
Well no. Alternative is to use templates. They provide you with single HTML file in which you can substitute strings.

Related:

  • http://forums.udacity.com/cs253-april2012/questions/7883/question-to-the-teachers-will-you-teach-how-to-use-html-templates
  • http://forums.udacity.com/cs253-april2012/questions/9973/how-to-use-the-jinja2-template-engine-with-appengine
  • https://developers.google.com/appengine/docs/python/gettingstarted/templates
